# Guards the PHI decision: this repository ships aggregate statistics only.
# The per-sample files stay out until the anonymisation work is done; see
# TODO_260719.md section 3 for what that involves and why.

# Background. Deny by default and allow only the three name-free aggregates,
# so any further file the importer emits stays out until it has been reviewed.
data/background/*
!data/background/backgroundStats.tsv
!data/background/backgroundCoverageStats.tsv
!data/background/backgroundMetricCoverage.tsv

# Any sample-name crosswalk, until the anonymisation work lands.
*crosswalk*

# Generated reports. These carry real sample names, so they are excluded both
# by output-directory convention and by filename, whatever --out is set to.
wgsTriage_out/
wgsTriage.txt
wgsTriage.html
wgsTriage_samples.tsv
wgsTriage_pairs.tsv

# The source archive is large and name-bearing; it is never part of the repo.
QCData/

# R
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rproj.user/
